    <item>
      <title>Amendments</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/governance/amendments/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/governance/amendments/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;PlainSight Lab does not treat governance as content. Governing documents are &lt;strong&gt;binding&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This page defines how changes occur to binding documents and how those changes are recorded.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If it is not amended through process, it is not changed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;1-what-can-be-amended&#34;&gt;1. What Can Be Amended&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Amendments apply to documents that are designated:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Active&lt;/strong&gt; in Docs, and/or&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;identified as canonical sources of truth (constitution, thesis, governance framework, policies)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Draft documents may be edited freely until they become Active.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
