    <item>
      <title>Internal Constitution</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/internal-constitution/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/internal-constitution/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;status&#34;&gt;Status&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Foundational governing document.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Not marketing.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This constitution defines the identity, authority boundaries, and self-binding obligations of PlainSight Lab. It exists to preserve correctness, prevent drift, and ensure legitimacy can be safely distributed over time.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This document is binding.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;article-i--purpose-and-scope&#34;&gt;Article I — Purpose and Scope&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;PlainSight Lab exists to anchor correctness in high-stakes systems where legitimacy is fragile and correction costs are high.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It is not a product company, a protocol, or a standards body. It is an epistemic and governance authority whose role is to establish, steward, and enforce invariants until those responsibilities can be safely transferred to formal, neutral institutions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
