    <item>
      <title>Problem Classes</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/problem-classes/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/problem-classes/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This document defines the formal &lt;strong&gt;Problem Classes&lt;/strong&gt; addressed by PlainSight Lab.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Problem classes are &lt;strong&gt;structural&lt;/strong&gt;, not domain-specific. They describe recurring failure modes that emerge across finance, AI systems, and social infrastructure when adversarial behavior, automation, and delayed correction interact.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A system may instantiate multiple problem classes simultaneously. Effective containment requires addressing &lt;strong&gt;all active classes&lt;/strong&gt;, not only the most visible one.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This registry exists to prevent misdiagnosis.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;pc-1-unbounded-error-propagation&#34;&gt;PC-1: Unbounded Error Propagation&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Definition&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;Systems in which errors propagate faster than humans can identify and correct them.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Responsible Disclosure Policy</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/responsible-disclosure-policy/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/responsible-disclosure-policy/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;purpose&#34;&gt;Purpose&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This policy defines how security, safety, and correctness issues should be responsibly disclosed to PlainSight Lab.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Its purpose is to:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;reduce harm,&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;preserve system integrity,&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;and enable correction before exploitation.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This policy is not a marketing instrument. It exists to support correctness under adversarial conditions.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;scope&#34;&gt;Scope&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This policy applies to disclosures related to:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;canonical specifications stewarded by PlainSight Lab,&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;derivative entities operating under its authority,&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;governance mechanisms or invariants,&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;and systems whose failure could cause material harm.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-to-disclose&#34;&gt;What to Disclose&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Responsible disclosure includes, but is not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
