    <item>
      <title>Security Posture</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/security-posture/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/security-posture/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;purpose&#34;&gt;Purpose&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This document defines the security posture of PlainSight Lab.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It describes how security is treated as a &lt;strong&gt;systems property&lt;/strong&gt;, not a checklist, and how adversarial risk is addressed through structure rather than reaction.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;core-assumptions&#34;&gt;Core Assumptions&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;PlainSight Lab operates under the following assumptions:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Adversarial behavior is normal, not exceptional.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Security failures compound faster than they are corrected.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Disclosure and correction costs matter as much as exploitability.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Trust must be earned through structure, not assertion.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Security is therefore a governance concern, not merely a technical one.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Stewards</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/governance/stewards/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/governance/stewards/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;stewards&#34;&gt;Stewards&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Stewardship roles within PlainSight Lab are constitutional offices.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;They exist to carry bounded authority in service of invariant preservation, correction discipline, and harm containment.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Stewardship is not ownership.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;It is not branding.&lt;br&gt;&#xA;It is not executive status.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It is accountable authority exercised within clearly defined limits.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Authority flows from the Constitution and governing documents — not from personality, reputation, or influence.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Stewardship is a constitutional burden, not a title.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
